### EC-OPS — Authentication
### Register a user and obtain a JWT Bearer token.
### Requires VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8002


# ── Register ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new user — returns 201 with user object
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "email": "admin@example.com"
}

###

### Register — duplicate username → 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "AnotherPass1!"
}

###

### Register — password too short → 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "baduser",
  "password": "short"
}


# ── Login (get JWT) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Login — returns { "access_token": "...", "token_type": "bearer" }
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin&password=Password1!

###

### Login — wrong password → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin&password=wrongpassword


# ── Test token ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the access_token value from the login response above,
# paste it below, then run any request in orders.http / agent.http.

@token = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### Verify token works — list orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### No token → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders

###

### Bad token → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer not.a.real.token
